Author: boldstop
Title: Ask YC: Do we need to file an amendment if we change our idea after incorporation?
Content:
We've decided to switch to another idea but while incorporating as a Delaware C-corp, we mentioned things that were specific to our original idea.

I know that changing ideas is not uncommon. Does anyone know a good way to go about this? Do we need to file an amendment? Re-incorporate?
